data.content:
2000
The year 2000 marks the narrator's birth and the beginning of their life with their grandfather.<SEP>The year 2000 marks the birth of the narrator and the endpoint of the final time loop where the narrator returns with the child to begin the cycle anew.

Child
The child is born to the narrator in 2024 and is immediately stolen after birth.<SEP>The child is the offspring of the narrator, later revealed to be another version of the narrator, and is stolen after birth to maintain the time loop.

Boyfriend
The boyfriend abandons the narrator in 2023 after learning about her unusual physical condition and reappears in 2027 following her surgery.<SEP>The boyfriend is the male version of the narrator from a different point in the time loop, who disappears after the narrator becomes pregnant at age 23.

Parents
The narrator's parents are unknown until the letter is opened in 2027, at which point their identity is revealed.

Narrator
The narrator is the central character who recounts key life events from 2000 to 2027, including being raised by their grandfather, becoming a parent, and discovering the identity of their parents.<SEP>The narrator is the central character who experiences a complex time-loop life involving gender transformation, self-parenting, and interactions with past and future versions of themselves.

Letter
The letter is given by the grandfather to the narrator before his death and is to be opened on the narrator's 27th birthday; it reveals the identity of the narrator's parents.<SEP>The letter is given by the grandfather to the narrator at age 9 and instructs the narrator to open it on their 27th birthday, revealing the truth about the time loop.

Masked Person
The masked person is responsible for the grandfather's death in 2009.<SEP>The masked person is the narrator's future self who kills the grandfather in 2009 to ensure the timeline remains intact.

Grandfather
The grandfather is the narrator's only known relative at birth and raises the narrator until his death in 2009; he leaves a letter to be opened on the narrator's 27th birthday.<SEP>The grandfather is a figure in the narrator's early life who is killed in 2009 by a masked version of the narrator and passes on a crucial letter before dying.

2009
The year 2009 is when the grandfather is killed by a masked person and gives the narrator the letter.<SEP>The year 2009 is when the grandfather is killed by the masked narrator, triggering key events in the timeline.

2027
The year 2027 is when the narrator survives a car accident, undergoes surgery, reunites with her boyfriend, and opens the letter revealing her parents' identity.

2024
The year 2024 is when the narrator gives birth and her child is stolen.<SEP>The year 2024 is when the narrator, now 42 years old, realizes they resemble their grandfather and completes the final stage of the loop.

2023
The year 2023 is when the narrator becomes pregnant and her boyfriend abandons her after learning about her special physical condition.<SEP>The year 2023 is when the narrator must ensure their female self becomes pregnant to continue the timeline.

Sh Sn
"Sh Sn" appears to be a mistranslation or typographical error in the original text, likely intended to mean "killed" (from Chinese ""); it is not a person or entity but a corrupted verb phrase.

Time Loop
The time loop is a recurring cycle in which the narrator travels to specific points in time to ensure their own existence and the continuity of events.

Car Accident
The car accident at age 27 causes the narrators complete physical transformation into a male and triggers the revelation of their true identity.

27th Birthday
The 27th birthday is the specific date when the narrator is instructed to open the letter from their grandfather, triggering key revelations about the time loop.

Gender Transformation
Gender transformation refers to the narrators shift from female to male identity, both biologically and through time-loop mechanics.
